title: 'I told him to get out': Coworker litters while carpooling home from work, driver teaches him a lesson by kicking him out 15 miles from home in 20-degree weather
description: You can't pick your coworkers, and sometimes, it feels like the universe is playing a cruel trick on you with the folks management decides to hire. Whether you're a new employee facing the harsh reality of your new incompetent coworkers or you're a seasoned vet taking in the absurdity of yet another unfit new hire, you know this struggle a little too well. You might've gotten stuck with the colleague who swoops in at the last second and takes all the credit for your work, or the colleague who takes five to seven business days to reply to a simple email, or even worse, the office food thief who swipes your lunch like it's no big deal. But how do you handle a coworker who doubles as a litterbug? That's a new one.This story takes the office drama to the streets (literally) when one coworker decided to toss his coffee cup out the car window during while carpooling to work, completely disregarding the driver's plea not to. Instead of turning a blind eye, the driver put an immediate stop to it (again, literally). What followed was a cold, awkward, and very expensive journey to the office for the litterbug.
author: Isabella Penn

title: Parents miss daughter's wedding while taking their 21-year-old son to a theme park, bride tells tells family and friends what they did: 'She never paid attention'
description: This bride caused a butterfly effect in her parent's lives after they missed their only daughter's wedding day. Sibling favoritism is usually a little more subtle than it is in this woman's family. In some families, it means that the parent will spend hours on the phone with one kid, while forgetting to even text another back. Or some daughters are the apple of their father's eye, but they just can't get along with their mom. There are a lot of complex family dynamics that contribute to this. And that's why for u/sh****-mom-throwaway, after years of tension, her wedding led to the entire family finally coming face to face with their blatant favoritism. Can you imagine missing your own child's wedding just because you didn't really feel like going? It's unimaginable to many parents: it's one of those sweet events that people really look forward to celebrating as the newlyweds usher in a new period of their lives. Not these parents, though: they treated their daughter's wedding as if she just invited them out for a casual coffee date, denying to show up at all! The story is quite long but well worth the read, as well as the update where things really started to change drastically for the original poster. Next, read about some other dramatic wedding moments, like one person who admitted that "The tornado at the outdoor reception was kinda bad."
author: Remy Millisky

title: 20 Cats Causing Chaos on Christmas Trees to Celebrate the Most Meownderful Time of the Year
description: It's that time again. The time of Christmas trees and lights and joy and chaos. So much chaos. Specifically to cat owners. Because everyone knows that for some reason, every year, cats decide to have a war with Christmas. Or maybe it's not a war. Maybe it's love that's making cats get inside of Christmas trees the second that they are put up. But everyone knows that love can lead to chaos, and the same is true for cats and Christmas trees.And so, another year, and the madness continues. It's only the beginning of December, and not all of us have put up their trees yet, but the ones of us who decided to start the party a little earlier than most are already experiencing the meowgic of Christmas, because cats don't care how early, they will get up on those Christmas trees and make sure that the party starts instantly.
author: Marielru

title: A Flurry of Fluffy Feline Funnies for Fuzzy Feline Expurrts to Purruse While Weathering the Cold Winter Winds
description: Brrrrrrrrr….it's cold outside, feline fam! All of a sudden, we're wrapped up in giant, poofy coats, bundled up in scarves and hats, and wishing we were back inside underneath the coziness of our comforters (well, that's nothing new). With this cold winter weather and the sun going down earlier and earlier, we can't be bothered to go outside at all. In fact, we've been inside so much that even our cats are starting to get tired of us! That's why we've collected a flurry of feline funnies for you to pursue while weathering the cold winter winds (from the warmth of your own home).No matter rain or shine, snow or sleet, these cold-weather cat memes are sure to keep your hearts and fingers warm while any sort of storm rages outside. Now we just need a cup of hot chocolate to keep us company while our cats take up the whole heater. Not only is it the purrfect day to stay inside, but it's also the purrfect day to scroll through these feline funnies. Enjoy!

title: Papa Gurgle
description: If you are a dork of a specific flavor, a subset of a subset, you might be watching a pretend advent calendar on the Warhammer Community site. Because wargames exist at the nexus of tiny plastic freaks and walls of text - with affection for either marking one as somewhat outside the bounds of society - adding a little bit more text can change everything about how these poles interact. Well, they're adding all kinds of text over there - Thousand Sons got some love today, my evil bugs got some love the day before, and a couple days ago Noah - who doesn't need any fucking help at all - got some new toys as well. He doesn't know, because he can't be allowed to know. It's for the best.

title: Error'd: Doubled Daniel
description: This week, a double dose of Daniel D. First he shared a lesson he titled "Offer you can't refuse a.k.a. Falsehood programmers believe about prices" explaining "Some programmers believe that new prices per month (when paid annually) are always better then the old ones (when paid monthly). Only this time they have forgotten their long-time clients on legacy packages."   Then he found a few more effs. "This e-shop required to create an account to download an invoice for order already delivered. Which is kind of WTF on its own. But when I pasted a generated 62 mixed character (alphanumeric+special) password, their form still insisted on entering 8+ characters. not correct. Well, because their programmers didn't expect somebody to paste a password. Once I did another JS event - e.g. clicked a submit button, it fixed itself."   And our Best Beastie in Black discovered "Anomalies in the causal structure of our particular 4-dimensional Lorentzian manifold have apparently caused this secure message portal belonging to a tax prep/audit company to count emails that haven't yet been sent by sender."   Traveler Tim R. struggled to pay for a visa, and reports this result. Rather than an error reported as success, we appear to have here a success reported as an error. "We're all familiar with apps that throw up an eror dialog with the error message as success but it's particularly irritating when trying to submit a payment. This is what happened when I tried to pay for an Indian visa with Paypal. To add insult to injury, when you try to pay again, it says that due to errors and network problems, you must check back in 2 hours before attempting a repeat payment."   Finally Robert H. is all charged up about Chevy shenanigans.
